Module it.polimi.ingsw.triton.launcher
Package it.polimi.ingsw.triton.launcher.server.controller.visitors

Class ClientMessageModifierVisitor

java.lang.Object
it.polimi.ingsw.triton.launcher.server.controller.visitors.ClientMessageModifierVisitor
public class ClientMessageModifierVisitor extends Object
ClientMessageModifierVisitor modifies parameters, basing on received messages. Exceptions thrown by methods are all caught by controller.

    • visitForModify

      public void visitForModify(MotherNatureReply message) throws IllegalClientInputException, EndGameException, ChangeTurnException
      Allows the current player to move mother nature with the specified number of steps, after receiving the reply from him.
      Parameters:
      message - the last message received.
      Throws:
      IllegalClientInputException - if the number of steps are uncorrected.
      EndGameException - if a player moved his last tower onto the island with mother nature or the island with mother nature merged with another island and, after that, remain only three groups of islands.
      ChangeTurnException - if the cloud tiles are not fully filled, and so the current player didn't have to draw students from them.

    • visitForModify

      public void visitForModify(CloudTileReply message) throws EndGameException, IllegalClientInputException, ChangeTurnException
      Allows the current player to choose a cloud tile to draw students from it, after receiving the reply from him.
      Parameters:
      message - the last message received.
      Throws:
      IllegalClientInputException - if the cloud tile is already empty or not available.
      EndGameException - if there aren't any assistant cards or the bag is empty.
      ChangeTurnException - when the current player has already chosen one of the available cloud tiles.

    • visitForModify

      public void visitForModify(UseCharacterCardRequest message) throws IllegalClientInputException, CharacterCardWithParametersException, EndGameException
      Allows the current player to play a character card, after receiving the request from him. If the character card requested from the player needs some parameters to build the effect, it asks them.
      Parameters:
      message - the last message received.
      Throws:
      IllegalClientInputException - if the specified character card is not available or the player has already played one.
      EndGameException - if the bag is empty after drawing students from it and deposited them on a character card.
      CharacterCardWithParametersException - if the specified character card needs some parameters to build the effect.
